reviewText: The first ever WWF Fully Loaded event took place in July 1998.  The main event was for the WWF Tag Team Championship.  Champions-Kane and Mankind defend their titles against WWF Champion-Stone Cold Steve Austin and the  Undertaker.  THE "Skin To Win" bikini contest between Sable and  Jacqueline.  This one had everyone on their knees...especially THE  MAN-Jerry "The King" Lawler.  In a 2 out of 3 falls match, WWF  Intercontinental Champion-The Rock puts his belt up against HHH.  This  match proves that the WWF does not know how to handle their real true  talent.  To put the two best conditioned athletes in the WWF today in a 2/3  match with a 30 minute time limit does not leave the match with too much of  an ending.  WWF European Champion-D-Lo Brown, in a non-title match, takes  on X-Pac in an excellent one on one encounter.  Scorpio and Faarooq team up  to face Terry Funk and Bradshaw.  Val Venis takes on Jeff Jarrett.  Vader  and Mark Henry go at it on a battle of the bulls.  L.O.D. 2000 vs. Paul  Ellering's D.O.A.  Plus, the Dungeon Match between Owen Hart and Ken  Shamrock with Dan "The Beast" Severn as the special referee.
Title: WWF: In Your House 23 - Fully Loaded VHS

reviewText: The WWF obviously didn't want to sell very many of this video, you just have to look at the front cover to prove it. The main event features Kane  and Mankind led by Paul Bearer put their WWF Tag Titles on the line against  Austin and Taker. The elements are all there it's just the main event never  really comes together, there are a lot better WWF videos to buy then this  one, and you must be fully loaded if you're gonna spend money on this lame  pay-per-view. Lazy booking by the WWF.
summary: A terrible event, just look at the cover to prove it!
Title: WWF: In Your House 23 - Fully Loaded VHS

reviewText: Hello out there welcome to this, this is a review as part of my Retro Wrestling Pay Per View reviews as you can see I am reviewing Fully Loaded 1998. Which I don't know why The WWF didn't just stick with this event longer than 3 years. If you're reading this you had to have just randomly came across this review or you grew up watching wrestling during The Attitude Era like I did. Or you never got to experience The Attitude Era & are interested. As always I like to tell the backstory leading into each event so Vince Russo continued with his layered storylines on The June 29th episode of RAW IS WAR Stone Cold Steve Austin defeated Kane to regain The WWF Championship. The Undertaker who was at ringside came into the ring after the match he got a Stunner as both Kane & The Undertaker got up they looked at each other. The following week on RAW IS WAR Undertaker challenged for The WWF Championship which Stone Cold Steve Austin accepted except Vince McMahon said he will decided The NO 1 Contender. He also made The Fully Loaded main event Stone Cold Steve Austin & The Undertaker vs Kane & Mankind. McMahon put The Undertaker, Kane & Mankind in a Triple Threat Match to decide The NO 1 Contender only The Undertaker didn't show up or so we thought. Mankind said he won't fight his new friend Kane. Kane attacked Mankind & got the win Kane unmasked & it turned out to be The Undertaker so that raised a lot of questions if Undertaker & Kane have made up & are working together. The following week on RAW IS WAR Kane & Mankind who were NO 1 Contenders for The WWF Tag Team Championship defeated The New Age Outlaws to win the titles. DX wanted The Outlaws to get another title shot right then. Triple H asked for 2 ringside enforcers Stone Cold Steve Austin & The Undertaker. During that match The Referee was knocked out Road Dogg had Kane rolled up Stone Cold went to count the pin but The Undertaker pulled him out of the ring when Kane had the pin Undertaker went to make the count but Stone Cold pulled The Undertaker out of the ring. Austin & The Undertaker had a stare down Mankind had a chair & was going to hit The Undertaker but Kane took the chair & hit Steve Austin & started beating him down while Undertaker went after Mankind to close the show. The next week on RAW IS WAR Vince McMahon wanted answers. He asked Undertaker if he & Kane are working together he also told him if he wants to be an ideal WWF Champion then you have to work within the system. He put The Undertaker in handicap match against Kane & Mankind. The Undertaker walked out McMahon put Stone Cold Steve Austin in the match. During the match The Undertaker returned & was in Austin's corner he had a chair Austin ducked & hit Kane. Austin took the chair laid Mankind out then he laid The Undertaker out to close the show. On The July 6th episode of RAW IS WAR D Generation X made fun of The Nation with their infamous parody. The following week on RAW IS WAR a 2 Out Of 3 Falls Match was made between The Rock & Triple H at Fully Loaded the next week on RAW IS WAR Triple H lost The WWF European Championship to D'Lo Brown when The Rock interfered & hit Triple H with The Rock Bottom. On The June 29th episode of RAW IS WAR Ken Shamrock was being interviewed Owen Hart came out he had injured Shamrock back in April. Owen Hart challenged Ken Shamrock to face him in his backyard. On The July 20th episode of RAW IS WAR it was announced that Ken Shamrock & Owen Hart would face each other in The Hart Dungeon & Dan Severn would be The Special Guest Referee. Owen Hart threw Ken Shamrock into some steel steps while his back was turned. After a match Owen Hart was chased by Ken Shamrock. On The June 29th episode of RAW IS WAR WWF decided to bury the irrelevant Road Warriors even more Paul Ellering returned only for him to turn on The Road Warriors & announce that he is managing The DOA. On The July 20th episode of RAW IS WAR Paul Ellering tried to run over Animal's leg with a Motorcycle but Hawk made the save. That is pretty much the backstory leading into this event. The buyrate was a 0.90 that is up from The In Your House Canadian Stampede event from July of 97 which got a 0.59The current champions in The WWF at the time wereWWF Champion Stone Cold Steve Austin June 29th 1998WWF Intercontinental Champion The Rock December 8th 1997 The Rock was awarded the title when then champion Stone Cold Steve Austin refused to defend the title against The Rock in a a mandatory title defense.WWF European Champion D'Lo Brown July 1998 14th match aired July 20th 1998WWF Tag Team Champions Kane & Mankind July 13th 1998Date July 26, 1998Attendance 9,855Venue Selland ArenaCity Fresno, CaliforniaFree For AllKevin Kelly interviewed who said don't expect the match to go 3 falls or a long match. He ended by saying that I'm you're daddy Rock.Michael Cole interviewed The Nation. The Rock said that he has Triple H right where he wants him he said The Rock is going into Fully Loaded as The Intercontinental Champion & he's going to leave Fully Loaded The Intercontinental Champion. Whether it's 2 Out Of 3, 5 Out Of 7 or 10 Out Of 15.D'Lo Brown said he has 2 words for X Pac non title. He added you think you can mess with Royalty you're going to get laid down by The D'Lo Brown. Mark Henry said it used to Vader Time now it's Mark Henry Time. The Godfather said that Owen's not a nugget & he's going to give Ken Shamrock a whoopin.Ad shown for The Stone Cold Baseball Jersey.Jerry Lawler interviewed Sable about The Bikini Contest she gave The King a peek which he enjoyed a little too much.Michael Cole interviewed Jerry "The King" Lawler he said that he ain't telling anybody about Sable's Bikini only to order The Pay Per View.A really good video package is shown for The WWF Tag Team title match.Michael Cole interviewed Stone Cold Steve Austin where he said that if The Undertaker thinks if he's going to take me down then I will take Son Of A B  *  *  *  h with him.A WWF Attitude spot was shown.The opening was very good.Val Venis Def Jeff Jarrett with Tennessee Lee ** an ok matchMr Yamaguchi San cause Yamaguchi San's Wife was sleeping with Val Venis. He promised tomorrow night on RAW Val Venis is in big trouble he's going to show him The Kaientai Style.After the match Val Venis got on the mic & said that Mr Yamaguchi San's Wife is right he will never measure up to The Big Valboski.D'Lo Brown with The Godfather Def X Pac with Chyna * & half of a starthis match could've been better had it had 5 more minutes & maybe the title was on the line.They show some guy named Edge in the crowd.Backstage Kevin Kelly announce's that The Undertaker has not arrived at the arena yet.Faarooq & 2 Cold Scorpio Def Def Bradshaw & Terry Funk * & 3 quarters of a star an ok match.Terry Funk announced that he was taking 6 months off which I guess meant he was going to show up in WCW about a year & half later & wouldn't be seen in The WWE until 05 or 06.The fans chanted boring during the match which I thought this match was ok with 2 or 3 cool spots & I have to wonder if The Internet Smarks are on to something when they say Attitude Era fanboys & fangirls weren't real wrestling fans.Bradshaw turned on Terry Funk 2 Cold Scorpio tried to stop him bur he got a big boot. Faarooq checked up on Scorpio Bradshaw hit his soon to be tag team partner with a steel chair.Mark Henry Def Vader * & half of a star a watchable match but you could tell Vader was on his way out.Kevin Kelly backstage announces that The Undertaker still hasn't arrived.Paul Bearer came out with Kane & Mankind. Paul Bearer said that The Undertaker is a coward he wants to be in 1 piece for Summerslam & Stone Cold is in the wrong place at the wrong time.The New Age Outlaws came out & challenged for The Tag titles on the next night on RAW. Then it turned into a brawl.The DOA Skull & 8 Ball with Paul Ellering Def The LOD 2000 * & 3 quarters of a star  another ok match & I can say this is 1 of The LOD vs DOA matches.Vince McMahon came out he said if The Undertaker no shows then blame Stone Cold Steve Austin & if The Undertaker no shows then The Brooklyn Brawler will be his replacement. Jim Ross said I thought he was in jail. The King said I think he made bail.Dungeon MatchOwen Hart Def Ken Shamrock ** & quarter of a star Dan "The Beast" Severn was The Special Guest RefereeShamrock accidentally hit Severn with kick Owen Hart took a Dumbbell hit Shamrock with it he took Shamrock's hand & made the motion he tapped out Dan Severn called the match for Owen Hart.2 Out Of 3 FallsWWF Intercontinental ChampionshipChampion The Rock 1 fall vs Triple H 1 fall with Chyna went to a draw *** & 3 quarters of a starTriple H hit The Pedigree but the time went out when he went for the cover.The Undertaker arrived to the arena during The Intercontinental title match.They show exclusive footage with The Rock gloating he said he went out there & showed why he was The BestD  a  mn Intercontinental Champion.Dustin Rhodes came out before The Bikini Contest to lead us all in prayer.Bikini ContestJacqueline with Marc Mero Def Sable by disqualificationI didn't tell the backstory about this match but this was an off shoot of The Marc Mero Sable storyline which had been going on way too long basically Jacqueline had been calling out Sable to face her in a Bikini Contest.You should all know what this was famous for.WWF Tag Team ChampionshipStone Cold Steve Austin & The Undertaker Def Champions Kane & Mankind with Paul Bearer ** & half of a starThe Undertaker started using different music at this pointThe Undertaker left with both Tag title beltsExclusive Footage shows him going backstage with both belts.This was an ok to decent Pay Per View it was throwaway but I got some enjoyment out of it. None of the matches were below a star the best match of the show was The 2 Out Of 3 Falls Match between The Rock & Triple H & it lead to The Ladder Match at Summerslam. The Tag Team title match was decent. Half way decent Dungeon Match with Owen Hart & Ken Shamrock. The opener with Jeff Jarrett & Val Venis was ok. A decent undercard while there was no matches I would call decent at least there were no half a star matches or DUD's it was throwaway like D Generation X In Your House but no where near as boring. If you see The VHS in a pawn shop really cheap & you really want to see this show then go ahead. Or if you can find a bootleg seller & want to see every WWF Pay Per View from 1998 then go ahead. Next I will be reviewing WWF Summerslam 1998 which I haven't seen since like 1999.
summary: WWF Fully Loaded In Your House review 6.5/10
Title: WWF: In Your House 23 - Fully Loaded VHS

reviewText: The Jeff Jarrett-Val Venis match was kind of boring but still good. The match between D-lo Brown & X-Pac had lots of high-flying action and it was pretty good. The Faarooq/Scorpio-Terry Funk/Justin Bradshaw tag team match was not great but pretty good and the same goes for the Vader-Mark Henry match. The D.O.A-L.O.D 2000 tag team match was slow & boring. The Owen Hart-Ken Shamrock-Dungeon match was a solid/back-and-forth bout even with Owen cheating at the end. The 2 out of 3 falls match for the IC between The Rock & HHH was a hard-hitting,back-and-forth,entertaing,smash-mouth match of the night. The Jacqueline-Sable-Bikini contest was pathetic & dirty. No matter how much men loved it. Leave those dumb constests for bars & beaches. The World tag team championship match between the team of The Undertaker & Steve Austin against the team of Kane & Mankind was a hard-hitting,smash-mouth,ruthless,entertaining tag team brawl. I give this PPV a 8 out of 10.
Title: WWF: In Your House 23 - Fully Loaded VHS

reviewText: 1998 Fully LoadedJuly 26, 1998Selland ArenaFresno, CaliforniaVal Venis V. Jeff JarrettGood watchable match that had it's high points. Venis wins. **3/4D'Lo Brown V. X-PacThis two all always solid in the ring against each other and this one is no exception. Good match with D'Lo going over. ***1/4Scorpio & Faarooq V. Terry Funk & Bradshawok match that had Scorpio & Funk doing some old ECW stuff. Scorpio & Faarooq win. **Vader V. Mark HenryWhat's with the Henry push? He beats a former World Champion in Vader and then beats the Rock in October. I really don't know what Vince sees in the guy. I think he is a useless talent. 1/2*LOD 2000 V. DOAThis is like the 900th time these two teams had met and every single match sucked and this one sucks also. DOA win. *Dungeon Match:Ken Shameock V. Owen HartAwesome. The Dungeon is tiny and not many people knew that before this match. Very solid wrestling with a very good ending. Owen wins, ***3/4...or course Owen is going to win, it is in his own house2-Out-Of-3 Falls Match for the WWF Intercontinental Championship:The Rock (Champion) V. Triple HThis match could have been better if the first fall came a little earier and didn't have a godamn time limit! Why would it have a time limit is behind me. So you guessed it...it ends in a time limit draw. ***3/4WWF Tag Team Championship:Kane & Mankind (Champions) V. Stone Cold Steve Austin & UnderakerWhy isn't the WWF Championship on the line? It would have been cool. Anyways we get a good Tag Team Match that really wasn't anything special but was solid. Austin & Undie win the titles. ***1/2Overall a godd show that had the only Dungeon Match and a bikini contest that everyone seems to remember more than the main event. I don't blame them.
summary: The WWF Champion In A Main Event Tag Team Match?...This Isn't WCW!!!!
